eighth day, the longest run of gains in more than five months,
before U.S. lawmakers vote this week on legislation pressing
China to raise the value of its currency.  Twelve-month contracts rose 0.3 percent to 6.5525 per
dollar as of 8:36 a.m. in Hong Kong, projecting a 2.4 percent
appreciation from the yuanâ€™s spot rate of 6.7079.  U.S. legislation to be voted on by the House on Sept. 29
